text: Vianen is a former municipality in the Dutch province of Utrecht, and of South Holland. The municipality was merged with the former municipalities of Leerdam and Zederik on 1 January 2019. The name of the new municipality is Vijfheerenlanden, which is a part of the province of Utrecht.
